{
  "page": "Sealord's menagerie",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Sealord's menagerie</b> is a famous collection of <a href=\"/index.php/Bestiary\" title=\"Bestiary\">animals</a> owned by the <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord of Braavos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sealord%27s_menagerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Description\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The magnificent beasts and birds, originating from throughout the <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">known world</a>, live in a <a href=\"/index.php/Menagerie\" title=\"Menagerie\">menagerie</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord%27s_Palace\" title=\"Sealord&#39;s Palace\">Sealord's Palace</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Braavosi <a href=\"/index.php/Ship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ship\">ship</a> captains often bring strange new animals they have found on their travels to the Sealord's menagerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sealord%27s_menagerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/54_AC\" title=\"54 AC\">54&#160;AC</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Elissa Farman\">Elissa Farman</a> sold three stolen <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon eggs</a> to the Sealord of Braavos, whose menagerie was famous.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Alyn%27s_attack\" title=\"Lord Alyn&#39;s attack\">Lord Alyn's attack</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Daughters%27_War\" title=\"Daughters&#39; War\">Daughters' War</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a> captured an <a href=\"/index.php/Elephant\" title=\"Elephant\">elephant</a> which had been meant for the Sealord's menagerie. On Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a>'s return to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, he rode the elephant through the <a href=\"/index.php/River_Gate\" title=\"River Gate\">River Gate</a> up to the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> while thousands of people lined the streets hoping to see their new hero. Alyn gifted the elephant to King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>, but Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Mooton\" title=\"Manfryd Mooton\">Manfryd Mooton</a> returned the elephant to the Sealord as part of his diplomatic efforts to prevent war.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sealord%27s_menagerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sealord%27s_menagerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Syrio_Forel\" title=\"Syrio Forel\">Syrio Forel</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> about the various unusual animals he has seen in the Sealord's menagerie. He explains that one day, the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Sword\" title=\"First Sword\">First Sword</a> of Braavos was recently dead, and the Sealord sent for Syrio. Many other <a href=\"/index.php/Bravo\" title=\"Bravo\">bravos</a> had been sent for, and then sent away, with no explanation given. When Syrio arrived at the palace, the Sealord was seated with a fat yellow <a href=\"/index.php/Cat\" title=\"Cat\">cat</a> in his lap. The Sealord claimed that the animal had been brought to him by a captain from an \"island beyond the sunrise\", and asked Syrio if he had ever seen anything like her. While the other bravos had described it as a large and fabulous beast with unusually small ears, Syrio was the only one to recognize the truth, and replied that it was merely a fat tomcat from the alleys of Braavos whose ears had been chewed away from kitten fights. To this, the Sealord laughed, and made Syrio his new First Sword.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sealord%27s_menagerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Hear me. The <a href=\"/index.php/Ship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ship\">ships</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> sail as far as the winds blow, to lands strange and wonderful, and when they return their captains fetch queer animals to the <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord</a>'s menagerie. Such animals as you have never seen, <a href=\"/index.php/Zorse\" title=\"Zorse\">striped horses</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/giraffe\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:giraffe\">great spotted things with necks as long as stilts</a>, hairy mouse-pigs as big as cows, stinging <a href=\"/index.php/Manticore\" title=\"Manticore\">manticores</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pouch_tiger\" title=\"Pouch tiger\">tigers that carry their cubs in a pouch</a>, terrible <a href=\"/index.php/Walking_lizard\" title=\"Walking lizard\">walking lizards</a> with scythes for claws. Syrio Forel has seen these things.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Syrio_Forel\" title=\"Syrio Forel\">Syrio Forel</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sealord%27s_menagerie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_50\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 50\">Chapter 50</a>, Arya IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; The Free Cities&#32;(Braavos).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfab9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfab9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Birth, Death, and Betrayal Under King Jaehaerys I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfab21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfab21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404041624\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.034 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.061 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 757/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8925/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3360/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 781/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion de